<plot>The film is devoted to the 50th anniversary of the saving of the Bulgarian Jews from Nazi genocide. The author looks in on the lives of three of his contemporaries: Simon Versano - a 38-year-old photographer; Abraham Behar - a 79-year-old rabbi; Iossif (Joseph) Surchadzhiev -a 49-year-old actor. The structure resembles three shorts united by the leitmotif of the preservation of human dignity in spite of life's vicissitudes.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?497592</url></doc>
